#Hapilin
a = open("Testo4.txt","r")
z = open("Testo4viv.txt","w")
for i in reversed(a.readlines()):
	z.write(str(i))
z.close()
a.close()

Testo4.txt
Beautiful is better than ugly.
Explicit is better than implicit.
Simple is better than complex.
Complex is better than complicated.

Testo4viv.txt
Complex is better than complicated.
Simple is better than complex.
Explicit is better than implicit.
Beautiful is better than ugly.
